		<h2 class="story">
				
				
				
			<span id="title-31583683"> <a   href="//science.slashdot.org/story/12/04/12/176200/ex-nasa-employees-accuse-agency-of-extreme-position-on-climate-change">Ex-NASA Employees Accuse Agency of 'Extreme Position' On Climate Change</a></span>
			
			
			<span class="comments commentcnt-31583683" >616</span>
			

                        
		</h2>
		<div class="details" id="details-31583683">
		
		Posted
		by 
	
	
		
			<a href="https://www.monkey.org/~timothy/" rel="nofollow">timothy</a>
		
	
	

	
	
	<time id="fhtime-31583683" datetime="on Thursday April 12, @01:51PM">on Thursday April 12, @01:51PM</time>
	
	
		<br>from the hi-dr-potocki! dept.
	
	</div>
	</header>

	<div class="body" id="fhbody-31583683">

		


			<div id="text-31583683" class="p">
			grumpyman writes <i>"A coalition of 49 ex-NASA employees, including seven Apollo astronauts, have <a href="https://news.nationalpost.com/2012/04/11/nasa-climate-change/">accused the U.S. space agency of sullying its reputation</a> by taking the 'extreme position' of concluding that carbon dioxide is a major cause of climate change.  Is the claim in this letter opinion or fact?"</i></div>
			

		
		
			
		
