	<div id="comment_top_39662075" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_39662075" name="comment_link_39662075" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2782855&amp;cid=39662075" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(39662075)" >Re:If It Is Fact ...</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_39662075" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 39662075); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Raul654">Raul654 <span class="uid">(453029)</span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_39662075">		
		on Thursday April 12, @02:32PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2782855&amp;cid=39662075">#39662075</a>)
		<small><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Raul654" title="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Raul654" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_39662075"><p>"it only takes one person with a cogent argument to disprove something." -- Wrong. It takes empirical evidence, not a cogent argument. The consensus view that the earth is getting warmer is backed by literally hundreds of published papers each of which cite physical evidence, measurement, models, etc. If there was a case to be made that the consensus view is wrong, there would have to be *some* evidence out there somewhere that contradicts the consensus view.  There is not, and that' is why there are no papers describing it.</p></div>
	</div>

